components.name: Extract Ensembl Mapping Files
components.description: Checks Ensembl FTP for new genomic mapping TSV.GZ files and downloads updated versions to the S3 raw landing zone.
outputs: Updated mapping files in S3 bucket cqgc-{env}-app-datalake under raw/landing/ensembl/

connections.purpose: Write downloaded files to S3 data lake

components.name: Process Ensembl Mapping with Spark
components.description: Runs a Spark job on Kubernetes to read the downloaded Ensembl mapping files from S3 and create structured Ensembl mapping tables in the data lake.
inputs: Mapping files in S3 raw landing zone (raw/landing/ensembl/)
outputs: Processed Ensembl mapping tables stored in the data lake (e.g., parquet or Hive tables)

upstream_policy.description: Executes after successful completion of extract_ensembl_mapping_files

connections.purpose: Read raw files and write processed tables to S3

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

mapping_types.description: List of Ensembl genomic mapping types to process (canonical, ena, entrez, refseq, uniprot)

s3_bucket_format.description: S3 bucket naming pattern, e.g., cqgc-{env}-app-datalake

s3_key_path.description: S3 key prefix for raw landing zone, e.g., raw/landing/ensembl/

ftp_server_path.description: FTP directory path for Ensembl files

spark_class.description: Fully qualified Spark class to execute

config_file.description: Configuration file for Spark job (e.g., config-etl-large)

table_name.description: Target table name for Ensembl mapping

kubernetes_context.description: Kubernetes execution context for Spark (e.g., K8sContext.ETL)

ENV.description: Environment placeholder used in bucket naming (e.g., dev, prod)

sources: Ensembl FTP server TSV.GZ mapping files (canonical, ena, entrez, refseq, uniprot) located at ftp://ftp.ensembl.org/pub/current_tsv/homo_sapiens
sinks: Processed Ensembl mapping tables stored in S3 data lake under s3://cqgc-{env}-app-datalake/processed/ensembl/ as Parquet/Delta tables
